ol","target":"recbHLkz06CSe3C4K","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recuaSqUsqm6AJOol","target":"recE9nWKk1vLR7zi1","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recuaSqUsqm6AJOol","target":"rec1ZMFtfbEvoGC73","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recuaSqUsqm6AJOol","target":"recsU2ZSdzBvDqzgI","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recuaSqUsqm6AJOol","target":"reczPjeq0UdahiRrn","label":"mentions"}],"verses":[{"id":"recPiNbSyo9zMaGLb","ref":"Rom.11.1","text":"I say then, Hath God cast away his people? God forbid. For I also am an Israelite, of the seed of Abraham, of the tribe of Benjamin.","year":60},{"id":"reccyF1GdLU9KuwLU","ref":"Rom.11.2","text":"God hath not cast away his people which he foreknew. Wot ye not what the scripture saith of Elias? how he maketh intercession to God against Israel, saying,","year":60},{"id":"rec4Ow3ACkyXPxuqs","ref":"Rom.11.3","text":"Lord, they have killed thy prophets, and digged down thine altars; and I am left alone, and they seek my life.","year":60},{"id":"recqfYrvPmFe8VTR1","ref":"Rom.11.4","text":"But what saith the answer of God unto him? I have reserved to myself seven thousand men, who have not bowed the knee to the image of Baal.","year":60},{"id":"recoEjkBCl3xxue9a","ref":"Rom.11.5","text":"Even so then at this present time also there is a remnant according to the election of grace.","year":60},{"id":"recFixq5e8n5lPvA2","ref":"Rom.11.6","text":"And if by grace, then is it no more of works: otherwise grace is no more grace. But if it be of works, then is it no more grace: otherwise work is no more work.","year":60},{"id":"rec4tLH5Kgv7RCk0T","ref":"Rom.11.7","text":"What then? Israel hath not obtained that which he seeketh for; but the election hath obtained it, and the rest were blinded","year":60},{"id":"recZpS9XpmGDvzcpP","ref":"Rom.11.8","text":"According as it is written, God hath given them the spirit of slumber, eyes that they should not see, and ears that they should not hear;) unto this day.","year":60}]}
